**emotional caption coming in 3…2..1... 

I’ve been trying to take the time to get through the comments, messages, and posts, to cherish this moment of love & support. And during that, I’ve realized how powerful words can be. And how powerful you can be. 

This world can be a dark place, and often times, so can the internet. Building an online community, no matter the size, has good and bad days. This past weekend has reminded me of the good. I didn’t realize the difference your presence can make in someone’s life, even if they’ve never met you. I didn’t fully realize my content could bring a moment of happiness, a moment of inspiration, or even just a laugh during a time when it’s needed most. That’s something worth fighting for, that’s something worth building, and that’s a dream worth chasing. 

I am overwhelmed by the amount of love and support I was shown through this Merch launch. A project I worked on for months, not knowing how it would be received, and scared to find out. The words I have received from people I’ve never met has touched my heart in ways I can’t explain. I feel connected to you, the same way you feel connected to me. 

There are pros and cons to social media. But one pro I am feeling more than ever is a community. You can have a group of people from all over the world rooting for you, feeling proud of you, feeling hurt for you, feeling happy for you… but they’ve never actually met you. This type of humanity is so unique, strange, and special. 
 
Thank you for being on this journey with me. Thank you for your support. YOU make MY days better, and you probably don’t even realize it. ❤️

100’000 SUBSCRIBERS ON YOUTUBE!!🥹✨ 
a milestone I’ve been dreaming about for a long time now. years later, and over 1000 uploads, we made it. Most people don’t know that I actually started my YouTube account in 2018 (swipe). At the time, I didn’t realize the potential I had and convinced myself no one really cared. Turns out I was wrong. People do care. You just have to find those people along the way. To those people, thank you. There’s no words to express my gratitude for the support on my content, my merch, and the time you take out of your day to watch me through a camera lens. Thank you for making this milestone happen. A huge thanks to my editors who not only have believed in my content, but have helped create it. You play a big part in this. And to my incredible friends and family, thanks for always encouraging me to be nothing less than myself, because apparently that’s enough. My Matty - thanks for believing in me more than I believe in myself. 🖤🎥

oh new york, how I’ve missed you🖤🍎

December 22nd will never feel like just another day, because it’s the day we lost Matts beautiful mother, Michelle. She was the mother-in-law a girlfriend could only dream about. She introduced me to everyone as her daughter-in-law, and although that’s technically not true yet, I loved playing the part. But with Michelle, there was no part to play. She loved me as if I was one of her own, and did the same with anyone who came into her life. Her heart, her humour, and her fight, will continue to inspire me. She never let me leave the house without a hug goodbye, hang up the phone without exchanging I love you’s, or flush the toilet without the lid closed. I feel so lucky to have experienced her love for the last 4 years. Forever wouldn’t have been long enough with a love like hers. we love you x1 million, and many more❤️
